{"id":"pseudo-code-ide-763.3","title":"GitHub Actions CI pipeline (lint → build → test → docker)","description":"Set up multi-stage GitHub Actions CI pipeline in .github/workflows/ci.yml.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [x] Stage 1: lint — runs eslint, fails fast\n- [x] Stage 2: build — compiles TypeScript + Vite, uploads dist artifact\n- [x] Stage 3: test — runs vitest unit tests (parallel with build)\n- [x] Stage 4: docker — builds and pushes image to ghcr.io on push to main only\n- [x] Pipeline triggers on push and pull_request to main\n- [x] Docker stage depends on both build and test passing","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"sriramn@thoughtworks.com","created_at":"2026-04-11T13:31:46Z","created_by":"N Sriram","updated_at":"2026-04-11T13:31:56Z","closed_at":"2026-04-11T13:31:56Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"pseudo-code-ide-763.3","depends_on_id":"pseudo-code-ide-763","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-11T19:01:45Z","created_by":"N Sriram","metadata":"{}"}]}
{"id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy","title":"Code Quality Gates","description":"Enforce code quality via ESLint security plugins (SAST) and 90% unit test coverage threshold in CI.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"sriramn@thoughtworks.com","created_at":"2026-04-11T13:42:06Z","created_by":"N Sriram","updated_at":"2026-04-11T13:42:06Z"}
{"id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy.1","title":"ESLint security plugins (SAST)","description":"Integrate ESLint security plugins into the existing lint pipeline as a SAST gate.\n\n## Plugins to add\n- eslint-plugin-security — flags unsafe JS patterns (eval, regex DoS, prototype pollution, etc.)\n- eslint-plugin-no-unsanitized — flags unsanitized DOM insertion (innerHTML, outerHTML, etc.)\n\n## Changes\n- Install both plugins as devDependencies\n- Add both plugins and their recommended rule sets to eslint.config.js\n- Verify `npm run lint` passes cleanly with new rules\n- CI lint stage already runs `npm run lint` — no CI changes needed\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] eslint-plugin-security and eslint-plugin-no-unsanitized installed\n- [ ] Both plugins active in eslint.config.js with recommended rules\n- [ ] `npm run lint` passes with zero errors\n- [ ] Any rule violations in existing code are either fixed or explicitly disabled with justification","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"sriramn@thoughtworks.com","created_at":"2026-04-11T13:42:14Z","created_by":"N Sriram","updated_at":"2026-04-11T13:59:53Z","closed_at":"2026-04-11T13:59:53Z","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["in_progress"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy.1","depends_on_id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-11T19:12:14Z","created_by":"N Sriram","metadata":"{}"}]}
{"id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy.2","title":"Unit test coverage threshold at 90%","description":"Enforce 90% unit test coverage as a CI quality gate.\n\n## Changes\n- Narrow coverage include to src/ only; exclude main.tsx and ast.ts (pure type definitions)\n- Add thresholds: statements 90, branches 90, functions 90, lines 90 in vitest.config.ts\n- Add tests for App.tsx (currently 0%) and validator.ts (currently 71.66%) to meet threshold\n- Update CI test stage to run `npm run test:coverage` and upload lcov artifact\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] vitest.config.ts has coverage include/exclude and thresholds configured\n- [ ] `npm run test:coverage` passes locally with all thresholds met\n- [ ] CI test stage runs coverage and fails build if threshold not met\n- [ ] lcov.info uploaded as CI artifact","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"sriramn@thoughtworks.com","created_at":"2026-04-11T13:42:32Z","created_by":"N Sriram","updated_at":"2026-04-11T13:42:32Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy.2","depends_on_id":"pseudo-code-ide-7zy","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-11T19:12:31Z","created_by":"N Sriram","metadata":"{}"}]}
